quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Strings[/h1]

A [b]string [/b]is an ordered sequence of characters, enclosed in [b]double quotation marks[/b]. 
It is part of the Standard Library. 
You need to include the [b]<string>[/b] library to use the string data type. Alternatively, you can use a library that includes the string library.[code format="cpp" codeId="217"][b]#include <string>[/b]
using namespace std;

int main() {
  [b]string [/b]a = "I am learning C++";
  return 0;
}[/code]
[note]The <string> library is included in the <iostream> library, so you don't need to include <string> separately, if you already use <iostream>.[/note]

